[1]
Date: Fri 17 Junn 2005
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organisation (WHO), CSR, Disease Outbreak News, Fri 17
Jun 2005 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_06_17a/en/print.html>

Viet Nam: Avian influenza Situation - WHO Update 22
--------------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health in Viet Nam has today confirmed that between 1 to 17
Jun 2005, 4 cases of human infection with H5N1 avian influenza virus were
reported. 2 of the patients are from Hanoi and one is from the nearby
province of Hai Duong. The 4th patient is from the central province of Nghe An.
All 4 of the patients are alive. At present, a total of 7 patients are
being treated for H5N1 avian influenza at a hospital in Hanoi.
These newly confirmed cases bring the total, in Viet Nam, since
mid-December 2004 to 59 cases, of which 18 were fatal.
--
